# library
library(tidyverse)
# Note: Loaded dataset contains continuous scores for each emotion from 30 individuals 

# Calculate average emotion scores for each emotion (Sad, Guilty, Shameful, Anxious, Wronged, Angry)
emotion_data <- emotion_data %>% 
  mutate(mean_sad = mean(Sad, na.rm = TRUE),
         mean_guilty = mean(Guilty, na.rm = TRUE),
         mean_shame = mean(Shameful, na.rm = TRUE),
         mean_anxious = mean(Anxious, na.rm = TRUE),
         mean_wronged = mean(Wronged, na.rm = TRUE),
         mean_angry = mean(Angry, na.rm = TRUE))

Density plot for each emotion with mean (average) values

Activity: How would you feel if you experienced internet abuse? (Sample size N = 30)

  • Sad (Scale: 0-10)
  • Guilt (Scale: 0-10)
  • Shame (Scale: 0-10)
  • Anxious (Scale: 0-10)
  • Wronged (Scale: 0-10)
  • Angry (Scale: 0-10)

Sad

ggplot(data = emotion_data, aes(x = Sad)) +        #plot x-axis, y-axis will be proportion by default in density plots
  geom_density(fill = "#4682b4", alpha = 0.3) +    #specify colour & transparency for density plot
  theme_light() +                                  #specify theme of plot
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = seq(0,10, by = 1)) + #specify the scale's interval for x-axis 
  labs(x = "Degree of Sadness", y = "Density/Proportion", title = "Distribution of Sad Emotion") + #include labels
  geom_vline(aes(xintercept = mean_sad), color = "darkgrey",linewidth = 0.5) + 
  #let mean value represented by a vertical line 
  geom_text(data = emotion_data, aes(x = mean_sad, y = 0.05, label = round(mean_sad, 3)), 
            #include mean value in the plot: x-coordinate set to the mean, y-coordinate set at 0.05, label set as displaying the mean value  
            color = "black", vjust = -1, hjust = -0.5, size = 3) # adjust vertical position(slightly above specified y-coordinate), horizontal position(slightly left of x-coordinate)
